cessary, <b>1-2 sec\/\/speed 5<b> until an even consistency is achieved. Transfer into Varoma dish and set aside."},{"content":"Place garlic, green onions, half the parsley and half the cilantro into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add mushrooms and wine and mix <b>10 sec\/\/speed 1<b>. Pour mushroom mixture over cauliflower in Varoma."},{"content":"Place water into mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket and weigh in yams."},{"content":"Secure Varoma lid, place Varoma into position and steam <b>15-18 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, or until yams are cooked. Remove Varoma, remove simmering basket with spatula and set yams aside to cool and drain for 5 minutes."},{"content":"Place a large serving bowl onto mixing bowl lid, weigh in currants and baby spinach."},{"content":"Add dried apricots, reserved spice-nut mixture, cooled cauliflower-mushroom mixture and cooled yams to serving bowl. Season to taste, then stir through remaining parsley and cilantro leaves with spatula."},{"content":"Serve immediately topped with reserved Parmesan cheese or cover and place in refrigerator until ready to use."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Serve Cauliflower Rice Pilaf with Yams as a main course, or as a side dish. It makes a great salad to take to your next barbecue or picnic.","Cauliflower rice is an easy grain-free alternative to rice when made in the Thermomix."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","4 portions"]}